==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Elide
<hw>E*lide"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Elided</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Eliding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>elidere</ets> to strike
out or off; <ets>e</ets> + <ets>laedere</ets> to hurt by striking: cf.
F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧lider</ets>. See <er>Lesion</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To break or dash in pieces; to demolish; <as>as, to <ex>elide</ex>
the force of an argument</as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Hooker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>To cut off, as a vowel or a
syllable, usually the final one; to subject to elision.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eligibility</ent>⟦br⟧
